A007734.name: Period of repeating digits of 1/n in base 3.

A007736.name: Period of repeating digits of 1/n in base 5.

A007737.name: Period of repeating digits of 1/n in base 6.

A007738.name: Period of repeating digits of 1/n in base 7.

A007739.name: Period of repeating digits of 1/n in base 8.

A007740.name: Period of repeating digits of 1/n in base 9.

A007741.name: a(n) = prime(n)*...*prime(m), the least product of consecutive primes which is abundant.
formula: a(n) = Product_{k=n..A007707(n)} prime(k) = Product_{0 <= i < A108227(n)} prime(n+i). - _M. F. Hasler_, Apr 30 2017 and Jun 15 2017

A007742.name: a(n) = n*(4*n+1).
formula: a(n) = A110654(n) + A173511(n) = A002943(n) - n. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Feb 20 2010

A007743.name: Number of n-celled mirror-symmetric solid polyominoes (or polycubes).

A007744.name: Expansion of (1+6*x)/(1-4*x)^(7/2).
formula: a(n) = binomial(2n+3, n) * binomial(n+3, 3). - _Paul Barry_, May 02 2005
D-finite with recurrence: n*a(n) + 2*(n-11)*a(n-1) + 12*(-2*n-1)*a(n-2) = 0. - _R. J. Mathar_, Nov 24 2012

A007745.name: a(n) = n OR n^2 (applied to binary expansions).

A007746.name: Number of ways for n-3 nonintersecting loops to cross a line 2n times.

A007747.name: Number of nonnegative integer points (p_1,p_2,...,p_n) in polytope defined by p_0 = p_{n+1} = 0, 2p_i - (p_{i+1} + p_{i-1}) <= 2, p_i >= 0, i=1,...,n. Number of score sequences in a chess tournament with n+1 players (with 3 outcomes for each game).
formula: Schoenfield (see Comments link) gives a recursive method for computing this sequence.

A007748.name: Number of self-converse oriented trees with n nodes.

A007749.name: Numbers n such that n!! - 1 is prime.

A007750.name: Nonnegative integers n such that n^2*(n+1)*(2*n+1)^2*(7*n+1)/36 is a square.

A007751.name: Even bisection of A007750.
formula: E.g.f.: (cosh(x) + sinh(x))*(-4 + (cosh(7*x) + sinh(7*x))*(4*cosh(3*sqrt(7)*x) + sqrt(7)*sinh(3*sqrt(7)*x)))/7. - _Stefano Spezia_, Feb 20 2020

A007754.name: Array (a frieze pattern) defined by a(n,k) = (a(n-1,k)*a(n-1,k+1) - 1) / a(n-2,k+1), read by antidiagonals.
formula: a(n, k) = (n+k)*a(n-1, k)-a(n-2, k) with a(0, k)=1 and a(-1, k)=0. - _Henry Bottomley_, Feb 28 2001
a(n, k) = Pi*(BesselJ(n+k+1, 2)*BesselY(k, 2) - BesselY(n+k+1, 2)*BesselJ(k, 2)). - Alec Mihailovs (alec(AT)mihailovs.com), Aug 21 2005
Column asymptotics (i.e. for fixed k and n -> infinity): a(n, k) ~ BesselJ(k, 2)*(n+k)!. - Alec Mihailovs (alec(AT)mihailovs.com), Aug 21 2005

A007755.name: Smallest number m such that the trajectory of m under iteration of Euler's totient function phi(n) [A000010] contains exactly n distinct numbers, including m and the fixed point.
formula: a(n) = smallest m such that A049108(m)=n.
Alternatively, a(n) = smallest m such that A003434(m)=n-1.

A007756.name: Number of irreducible indecomposable spherical curves with n crossings (only ordinary double points), the circle is oriented, the sphere is not oriented (OU case).

A007759.name: Knopfmacher expansion of sqrt(2): a(2n) = 2*(a(2n-1) + 1)^2 - 1, a(2n+1) = 2*(a(2n)^2 - 1).

A007760.name: Number of solid partitions of height n in a cube of side n.

A007762.name: Number of domino tilings of a certain region.

A007763.name: Number of pairs of length n permutations achievable by double-ended priority queue.

A007764.name: Number of nonintersecting (or self-avoiding) rook paths joining opposite corners of an n X n grid.

A007765.name: Primes p == 1 (mod 8), p = a^2 +64*b^2 such that y^2 = x^3 + p*x has rank 0.

A007766.name: Primes p == 1 (mod 8), p = a^2 + 64*b^2 such that y^2 = x^3 + p*x has rank 2.

A007767.name: Number of pairs of permutations of degree n that avoid (12,21).
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n!} k * A263754(n,k). - _Alois P. Heinz_, Jun 06 2016

A007769.name: Number of chord diagrams with n chords; number of pairings on a necklace.
formula: 2n a_n = Sum_{2n=pq} alpha(p, q)phi(q), phi = Euler function, alpha(p, q) = Sum_{k >= 0} binomial(p, 2k) q^k (2k-1)!! if q even, = q^{p/2} (p-1)!! if q odd.

A007770.name: Happy numbers: numbers whose trajectory under iteration of sum of squares of digits map (see A003132) includes 1.
formula: 1) Every power 10^k is a member of the sequence.
2) If n is member the numbers obtained by placing zeros anywhere in n are members.
3) If n is member each permutation of digits of n gives another member.
4) If the repeated process of summing squared digits give a number which is already a member of sequence the starting number belongs to the sequence.
5) If n is a member the repunit consisting of n 1's is a member.
6) If n is a member delete any digit d, new number consisting of remaining digits of n and d^2 1's placed everywhere to n is a member.
7) It is conjectured that the sequence includes an infinite number of primes (see A035497).
8) For any starting number the repeated process of summing squared digits ends with 1 or gives an "8-loop" which ends with (37,58,89,145,42,20,4,16,37) (End)

A007771.name: Values of Ehrhart polynomial of dilation by 2 of Relaxed Boolean Quadric Polytope of order 4.

A007772.name: Values of Ehrhart polynomial of dilation by 2 of Relaxed Boolean Quadric Polytope of order 3.

A007773.name: For any circular arrangement of 0..n-1, let S = sum of squares of every sum of two contiguous numbers; then a(n) = # of distinct values of S.

A007774.name: Numbers that are divisible by exactly 2 different primes.

A007775.name: Numbers not divisible by 2, 3 or 5.
formula: Numbers k such that ((k^2 mod 48=1) or (k^2 mod 48=25)) and ((k^2 mod 120=1) or (k^2 mod 120=49)). - _Gary Detlefs_, Dec 30 2011
Numbers k such that k^2 mod 30 is 1 or 19. - _Gary Detlefs_, Dec 31 2011
a(n) = 3*(floor((5*n-2)/4) - floor((n mod 8)/6)) + (n mod 2) + floor(((n-1) mod 8)/7) - floor(((n-2) mod 8)/7) + 1. - _Gary Detlefs_, Jan 08 2012

a(n) = 4*n - 3 + 2*(floor((n+6)/8) - floor((n+4)/8) - floor((n+2)/8) + floor(n/8) - floor((n-1)/8)), n >= 1. From the o.g.f. given above by _R. J. Mathar_ (with the denominator written as (1-x^8)*(1-x)), and a two-step reduction of the floor functions. Compare with Hopper's and Detlefs's formulas above. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, Jan 26 2012
a(n) = (6*f(n) - 3 + (-1)^f(n))/2, where f(n)= n + floor(n/4)+ floor(((n+4) mod 8)/6). - _Gary Detlefs_, Sep 15 2013
a(n) = 3*n + 6*floor(n/8) + (n mod 2) - 2*floor(((n-2) mod 8)/6) - 2*floor(((n-2) mod 8)/7) + 1. - _Gary Detlefs_, Jun 01 2014
a(n+1) = ((n << 2 - n >> 2) || 1) + ((n << 1 - n >> 1) && 2), where << and >> are bitwise left and right shifts, || and && are bitwise "or" and "and". - _Andrew Lelechenko_, Jul 08 2017

A007776.name: Number of connected posets with n elements of height 1.
formula: Inverse Euler transform of A055192. - _Andrew Howroyd_, Oct 03 2018

A007777.name: Number of overlap-free binary words of length n.

A007778.name: a(n) = n^(n+1).
formula: E.g.f.: -W(-x)/(1 + W(-x))^3, W(x) Lambert's function (principal branch).
See A008517 and A134991 for similar e.g.f.s. and A048993. - _Tom Copeland_, Oct 03 2011
E.g.f.: d/dx {x/(T(x)*(1-T(x))}, where T(x) = sum {n >= 1} n^(n-1)*x^n/n! is the tree function of A000169. - _Peter Bala_, Aug 05 2012

A007779.name: Coefficients of asymptotic expansion of Ramanujan false theta series.
formula: Sum_{n=0..infinity} a(n)x^n = (1-x^2)^{-1/4} (1+x)^{1/2} sum_{k=0..infinity) E_{2k} v^k/k!, where E_{2k} is an Euler number and v = (1/4)log((1+x)/(1-x)). - _Richard Stanley_, Jan 22 2006
Berndt gives an explicit g.f. on page 547.

A007780.name: Losing initial configurations in 2-hole Tchuka Ruma.

A007781.name: a(n) = (n+1)^(n+1) - n^n for n>0, a(0) = 1.
formula: E.g.f.: W(-x)/(1+W(-x)) - W(-x)/((1+W(-x))^3*x) where W is the Lambert W function. - _Robert Israel_, Aug 19 2015

A007782.name: Number of factors in the infinite word formed by the Kolakoski sequence A000002.

A007783.name: Mixed Van der Waerden numbers w(n, 3; 2).

A007785.name: Number of sets of positive integers <= n^2 whose sum is (n^3 + n)/2.

A007786.name: Number of nonintersecting rook paths joining opposite corners of 4 X n board.

A007787.name: Number of nonintersecting rook paths joining opposite corners of 5 X n board.
formula: Faase gives a 27-term linear recurrence on his web page:

A007788.name: Number of augmented Andre 3-signed permutations: E.g.f. (1-sin(3*x))^(-1/3).

A007789.name: From a problem concerning circulant matrices and Gauss sums.

A007790.name: From a problem concerning circulant matrices and Gauss sums.

A007791.name: From a problem concerning circulant matrices and Gauss sums.

A007792.name: From a problem concerning circulant matrices and Gauss sums.

A007793.name: Number of conjugacy classes of compact Cartan subgroups in Sp_{2n}(F), where p>n and the p-adic field F contains all r-th roots of unity for all r <= 2n.

A007796.name: List of pairs of primes in reverse order, starting at 1.

A007797.name: List of pairs of primes in reverse order.

A007798.name: Expected number of random moves in Tower of Hanoi problem with n disks starting with a randomly chosen position and ending at a position with all disks on the same peg.
formula: a(n) = (5^n - 2*3^n + 1) / 4. - _Henry Bottomley_, Jun 06 2000, proved by _Max Alekseyev_, Feb 04 2008

A007799.name: Irregular triangle read by rows: Whitney numbers of the second kind a(n,k), n >= 1, k >= 0, for the star poset.
formula: a(n,0) = 1, a(n,1) = n - 1, a(n,2) = (n-1)(n-2); a(n,i) = (n-1)a(n-1, i-1) + Sum_{j=1 .. n-2} j a(j, i-3). For 0 <= i <= ceiling(3(n-1)/2) and n >= 1 we have Sum_{k=0 .. i+1} (-1)^k binomial(i+1, k) a(n+i+1-k, i) = 0. For example, for i=2, we have a(n+3, 2) - 3a(n+2, 2) + 3a(n+1, 2) - a(n, 2) = 0. - Ke Qiu (kqiu(AT)brocku.ca), Feb 06 2005

A007800.name: From a problem in AI planning: a(n) = 4+a(n-1)+a(n-2)+a(n-3)+a(n-4)-a(n-5)-a(n-6)-a(n-7), n>7.

A007801.name: Expansion of f(f(x)), where f = x + x^2 + x^4 + x^8 + x^16 + ...

A007802.name: Numbers n such that game of n X n Button Madness need have no solution; this lists only the primitive elements of the set.

A007803.name: Number of connected series-parallel graphs with a longest path of at most n edges and also a largest cut set of at most n edges.

A007804.name: Related to the asymptotic expansion of Sum_{k = 0..n} C(n,k)^4.

A007805.name: a(n) = Fibonacci(6*n+3)/2.
formula: Let q(n, x) = Sum_{i=0..n} x^(n-i)*binomial(2*n-i, i); then a(n) = q(n, 16). - _Benoit Cloitre_, Dec 06 2002
a(n) = b(n+1) - b(n), n >= 0, with b(n) := F(6*n)/F(6) = A049660(n). First differences. See the o.g.f.s. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, 2012
a(n) = S(n,18) - S(n-1,18) with the Chebyshev S-polynomials (A049310). - _Wolfdieter Lang_, Jun 20 2013
Sum_{n >= 1} 1/( a(n) - 1/a(n) ) = 1/4^2. Compare with A001519 and A097843. - _Peter Bala_, Nov 29 2013
a(n) = 9*a(n-1) + 8*A049629(n-1), n >= 1, a(0) = 1. This is just the rewritten Chebyshev S(n, 18) recurrence. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, Aug 26 2014
a(n) = ( Fibonacci(6*n + 6 - 2*k) - Fibonacci(6*n + 2*k) )/( Fibonacci(6 - 2*k) - Fibonacci(2*k) ), for k an arbitrary integer.
a(n) = ( Fibonacci(6*n + 6 - 2*k - 1) + Fibonacci(6*n + 2*k + 1) )/( Fibonacci(6 - 2*k - 1) + Fibonacci(2*k + 1) ), for k an arbitrary integer.

The aerated sequence (b(n)) n>=1 = [1, 0, 17, 0, 305, 0, 5473, 0, ...] is a fourth-order linear divisibility sequence; that is, if n | m then b(n) | b(m). It is the case P1 = 0, P2 = -20, Q = 1 of the 3-parameter family of divisibility sequences found by Williams and Guy. See A100047 for the connection with Chebyshev polynomials. (End)

A007807.name: A variation on Euclid: a(n)=g(n)-1, where g(0)=0, g(1)=1, g(n+1)=g(n)(g(n-1)+1).
formula: a(n) = A005831(n) - 1 for all n>0. - _Michael Somos_, Jan 17 2015

A007808.name: Number of directed column-convex polyominoes of height n: a(k+1)=(k+1)*a(k)+(a(1)+...+a(k)).
formula: Conjectures: E.g.f.: (-(x^2+1)*exp(-x)+1)*exp(x)/(-1+x)^2; a(n) = round(n!*n*(exp(1)-2)). - _Simon Plouffe_, Dec 08 2009
Asymptotic approximation: a(n) ~ n!(1 + (n - 1)(e - 2)). - _Walden Freedman_, Aug 23 2014

A007809.name: Smallest prime with n distinct digits.

A007810.name: Largest prime with n distinct decimal digits.

A007811.name: Numbers n for which 10n+1, 10n+3, 10n+7 and 10n+9 are primes.

A007812.name: Number of n-node Steinhaus graphs whose complements have at least one cut-vertex.

A007813.name: Number of planar Steinhaus graphs with n nodes.

A007814.name: Exponent of highest power of 2 dividing n, a.k.a. the binary carry sequence, the ruler sequence, or the 2-adic valuation of n.
formula: a(n) = 0 if n is odd, otherwise 1 + a(n/2). - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Aug 11 2001
Sum_{k=1..n} a(k) = n - A000120(n). - _Benoit Cloitre_, Oct 19 2002
G.f.: A(x) = Sum_{k>=1} x^(2^k)/(1-x^(2^k)). - _Ralf Stephan_, Apr 10 2002
G.f. A(x) satisfies A(x) = A(x^2) + x^2/(1-x^2). A(x) = B(x^2) = B(x) - x/(1-x), where B(x) is the g.f. for A001151. - _Franklin T. Adams-Watters_, Feb 09 2006
Totally additive with a(p) = 1 if p = 2, 0 otherwise.
For n>=1, a(A004760(n+1)) = a(n). - _Vladimir Shevelev_, Apr 15 2009
a(C(n,k)) = A000120(k) + A000120(n-k) - A000120(n). - _Vladimir Shevelev_, Jul 19 2009
a(n) mod 2 = A096268(n-1). - _Robert G. Wilson v_, Jan 18 2012
a((2*n-1)*2^p) = p, p >= 0 and n >= 1. - _Johannes W. Meijer_, Feb 04 2013
a(n) = log_2(n - (n AND n-1)). - _Gary Detlefs_, Jun 13 2014
a(n) = 1 + A000120(n-1) - A000120(n), where A000120 is the Hamming weight function. - _Stanislav Sykora_, Jul 14 2014
a((2*x-1)*2^n) = a((2*y-1)*2^n) for positive n, x and y. - _Juri-Stepan Gerasimov_, Aug 04 2016
a(n) = A000005(n)/(A000005(2*n) - A000005(n)) - 1. - conjectured by _Velin Yanev_, Jun 30 2017, proved by _Nicholas Stearns_, Sep 11 2017
Equivalently to above formula, a(n) = A183063(n) / A001227(n), i.e., a(n) is the number of even divisors of n divided by number of odd divisors of n. - _Franklin T. Adams-Watters_, Oct 31 2018
Asymptotic mean: lim_{m->oo} (1/m) * Sum_{k=1..m} a(k) = 1. - _Amiram Eldar_, Jul 11 2020

A007815.name: Number of triangulations of cyclic 3-polytope C(3,n+3).

A007816.name: Number of abstract simplicial 2-complexes on {1,2,3,...,n+3} which triangulate the 2-sphere: C(n+3,2)*(4n+1)!/(3n+3)!.

A007817.name: Number of abstract simplicial 2-complexes on {1,2,3,...,n+4} which triangulate a Moebius band in such a way that all vertices lie on the boundary and are traversed in the order 1,2,3,... as one goes around the boundary.
formula: G.f.: x^2*((2-5*x-4*x^2)+sqrt(1-4*x)*(-2+x+2*x^2))/((1-4*x)*(1-4*x+2*x^2+sqrt(1-4*x)*(1-2*x))). [from the Stanley reference, _Joerg Arndt_, Apr 20 2011]

A007818.name: Maximal number of bonds joining n nodes in simple cubic lattice.

A007820.name: Stirling numbers of second kind S(2n,n).
formula: Asymptotic: a(n) ~ (4*n/(e*z*(2-z)))^n/sqrt(2*Pi*n*(z-1)), where z = A256500 = 1.59362426... is a root of the equation exp(z)*(2-z)=2. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, May 30 2011
O.g.f.: Sum_{n>=1} (n^2)^n * exp(-n^2*x) * x^n/n! = Sum_{n>=1} S2(2*n,n)*x^n. - _Paul D. Hanna_, Oct 17 2012
G.f.: sum(n>0, a(n)*n!/(2*n)!) = x*B'(x)/B(x)-1, where B(x) satisfies B(x)^2 = x*(exp(B(x))-1). - _Vladimir Kruchinin_, Mar 13 2013

A007821.name: Primes p such that pi(p) is not prime.
formula: A137588(a(n)) = n; a(n) = A000040(A018252(n)). - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Jan 28 2008
A000040 = A007821 U A006450. - _Juri-Stepan Gerasimov_, Sep 24 2009
A175247 U { a(n); n > 1 } = A000040. { a(n) } = { 2 } U { primes (A000040) with composite index (A002808) }. - _Jaroslav Krizek_, Mar 13 2010
G.f. over nonprime powers: Sum_{k >= 1} prime(k)*x^k-prime(prime(k))*x^prime(k). - _Benedict W. J. Irwin_, Jun 11 2016

A007822.name: Number of symmetric foldings of 2n+1 stamps.

A007824.name: a(n) = f(a(n-1)), with f(m) = Sum i*b(i)*2^(i-1), m = Sum b(i)*2^i, and starting value 16.

A007825.name: Number of n step self-avoiding walks on 3 X infinity grid starting from (0,1).

A007826.name: Numbered stops on the Market-Frankford rapid transit (SEPTA) railway line in Philadelphia, PA USA.
formula: a(n) = 2 + 3 n - binomial(n, 4) + 3 binomial(n, 5) + 7 binomial(n, 6) - 66 binomial(n, 7) + 248 binomial(n, 8) - 679 binomial(n, 9) + 1554 binomial(n, 10) - 3158 binomial(n, 11) + 5897 binomial(n, 12) - 10352 binomial(n, 13) + 17384 binomial(n, 14).

A007827.name: Number of homeomorphically irreducible (or series-reduced) trees with n pendant nodes, or continua with n non-cut points, or leaves.

A007828.name: Largest t such that a spherical t-design with n points exists in 3 dimensions.

A007829.name: From random walks on complete directed triangle.
formula: a(n) = 2*(2 + Fibonacci(n+2) - 2^floor(n/2) - b(n+7) - b(n+5)), where b(n) = A000931(n). (End)

A007830.name: a(n) = (n+3)^n.
formula: E.g.f. for b(n) = a(n-3): T(x)-(3/4)T^2(x)+(1/6)T^3(x), where T(x) is Euler's tree function (see A000169). - _Len Smiley_, Nov 17 2001

A007831.name: Number of edge-labeled series-reduced trees with n nodes.
formula: a(n) = A005512(n+1) / (n+1) for n >= 2. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Feb 03 2018

A007832.name: Number of point labeled 5,6-free two-graphs with n nodes.
formula: STIRLING transform of A007831. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Feb 03 2018

A007833.name: Number of point-labeled reduced two-graphs with n nodes.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} s(n, k) * 2^((k-1) * (k-2) / 2) where s(n, k) are the Stirling numbers of the first kind. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Feb 03 2018

A007834.name: Number of point labeled reduced 5-free two-graphs with n nodes.

A007835.name: Number of unordered sets of pairs (in-degree, out-degree) for nodes of directed trees on n unlabeled nodes (the edges are directed in arbitrary directions, the tree is unrooted).

A007836.name: Springer numbers associated with symplectic group.

A007837.name: Number of partitions of n-set with distinct block sizes.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} (n-1)!/(n-k)!*b(k)*a(n-k), where b(k) = Sum_{d divides k} (-d)*(-d!)^(-k/d) and a(0) = 1. - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Oct 13 2002

A007838.name: Number of permutations of n elements with distinct cycle lengths.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} (n-1)!/(n-k)!*b(k)*a(n-k), where b(k) = Sum_{d divides k} (-d)^(1-k/d) and a(0) = 1. - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Oct 13 2002
Asymptotics: a(n) ~ n!(e^{-g} + e^{-g}/n + O((log n)/n^2)), where g is the Euler gamma.

A007839.name: Number of polynomials of degree n over GF(2) in which the degrees of all irreducible factors are distinct.
formula: G.f.: Product_{m>=1} (1 + pi(m) x^m), where pi(m) = A001037(m) = number of distinct irreducible polynomials of degree m.

A007840.name: Number of factorizations of permutations of n letters into ordered cycles.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} k! * s(n, k), s(n, k) = unsigned Stirling number of first kind; E.g.f. 1/(1+log(1-z)).
For n>0, a(n) is the permanent of the n X n matrix with entries a(i, i) = i and a(i, j) = 1 elsewhere. - _Philippe Deléham_, Dec 09 2003
a(n) = n!*Sum_{k=0..n-1} a(k)/k!/(n-k) for n >= 1 with a(0)=1. - _Paul D. Hanna_, Jul 19 2006
E.g.f.: B(A(x)) where B(x) = 1/(1-x) and A(x) = log(1/(1-x)). - _Geoffrey Critzer_, Mar 18 2009
a(n) = D^n(1/(1-x)) evaluated at x = 0, where D is the operator exp(x)*d/dx. Cf. A006252. - _Peter Bala_, Nov 25 2011

A007841.name: Number of factorizations of permutations of n letters into cycles in nondecreasing length order.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} (n-1)!/(n-k)!*b(k)*a(n-k), where b(k) = Sum_{d divides k} d^(1-k/d) and a(0) = 1. - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Oct 14 2002
a(n) = R(n,1), R(n,m) = R(n,m+1)+binomial(n,m)*(m-1)!*R(n-m,m), R(n,n)=(n-1)!, R(n,m)=0 for n<m. - _Vladimir Kruchinin_, Sep 09 2014
a(n) ~ c * n! * n, where c = exp(-gamma) = 0.56145948..., where gamma is the Euler-Mascheroni constant A001620 [Lehmer, 1972]. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Mar 05 2016
E.g.f.: exp(Sum_{k>=1} Sum_{j>=1} x^(j*k)/(k*j^k)). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, May 27 2018

A007842.name: Largest determinant of 2n+1 X 2n+1 matrix with entries +-1 and 0 diagonal.

A007843.name: Least positive integer k for which 2^n divides k!.
formula: a(n) = A002034(2^n). For n>1, it appears that a(n+1) = a(n)+2 if n is in A005187. - _Benoit Cloitre_, Sep 01 2002
a(n) = 2*A046699(n) for n > 0. - _Michel Marcus_ and _M. F. Hasler_, Dec 27 2019

A007844.name: Least positive integer k for which 3^n divides k!.

A007845.name: Least positive integer k for which 5^n divides k!.

A007846.name: There are three equivalent descriptions: 1. Number of (horizontally or vertically) connected arrays of 1..n on rectangular grid (otherwise zero) with only one local maximum. 2. Number of n-polyominoes labeled 1...n such that each successive labeled cell is the neighbor of a previously labeled cell. 3. Number of connected n-step paths on a rectangular lattice, diagonal or repeated steps not allowed.

A007847.name: Number of hyperplanes spanned by the vertices of an n-cube.

A007848.name: Number of skew hyperplanes spanned by the vertices of an n-cube.

A007849.name: Number of hyperplanes spanned by the vertices of an n-cube that cover exactly n vertices.

A007850.name: Giuga numbers: composite numbers n such that p divides n/p - 1 for every prime divisor p of n.

A007851.name: Number of elements w of the Weyl group D(n) such that the roots sent negative by w span an Abelian subalgebra of the Lie algebra.
formula: a(n) = (n+3)*C(n)/2 - 1, where C(n) is a Catalan number (see A000108).

A007852.name: Antichains in rooted plane trees on n nodes.
formula: a(1) = 1 and for n > 1 a(n) = sum( (a(j)+b(j))*a(n-j), j=1..n-1 ), where b(n) = C(2n-2, n-1)/n (Catalan number).
Also REVERT[A(x)] = x + 2*x^2 + x^3*(A007440(x) (Reversion of Fibonacci). - _Olivier Gérard_, Jul 05 2001
a(n+1) = Sum_{k, 0<=k<=n} A039599(n,k) * A000108(k). - _Philippe Deléham_, Mar 12 2007

A007853.name: Number of maximal antichains in rooted plane trees on n nodes.
formula: G.f.: (1/4) * (3 - 2*x - sqrt(1-4*x) - sqrt(2) * sqrt((1+2*x) * sqrt(1-4*x) + 1 - 8*x + 2*x^2)) [from Klazar]. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Feb 06 2018
Given the g.f. A(x) and the g.f. of A213705 B(x), then -x = A(-B(x)). - _Michael Somos_, Nov 07 2019

A007854.name: G.f.: 1/(1 - 3*x*C(x)), where C(x) = (1 - sqrt(1 - 4*x))/(2*x) = g.f. for the Catalan numbers A000108.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k>=0} A106566(n, k)*3^k. - _Philippe Deléham_, Aug 11 2005
The Hankel transform of this sequence is A000244 = [1, 3, 9, 27, 81, 243, 729, ...](powers of 3). - _Philippe Deléham_, Nov 26 2006
a(n) = upper left term in M^n, M = the infinite square production matrix:

A007855.name: Infima closed sets in rooted plane trees on n nodes.
formula: G.f.: (1/4) * (1 + sqrt(1-4*x)) * (1 - sqrt(3 - 2 / sqrt(1-4*x))) [from Klazar]. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Feb 06 2018

A007856.name: Subtrees in rooted plane trees on n nodes.
formula: G.f.: (1/8) * (1 + 1/sqrt(1-4*x)) * (1 + sqrt(1-4*x) - sqrt(2) * sqrt(1 - 10*x + sqrt(1-4*x))), see Klazar's paper. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Feb 06 2018

A007857.name: Number of independent sets in rooted plane trees on n nodes.
formula: G.f.: A(x) = x/(1 - x*C(x)*F(x) - x*F(x)^2), where C(x) is g.f. of the Catalan numbers (A000108) (i.e., C(x) = 1 + x*C(x)^2) and F(x) is the g.f. of ternary numbers (A001764) (i.e., F(x) = 1 + x*F(x)^3). - _Paul D. Hanna_, Jun 06 2007

A007858.name: G.f. is 1 - 1/f(x), where f(x) = 1+x+3*x^2+9*x^3+32*x^4+... is 1/x times g.f. for A063020.
formula: a(n+1) = Sum_{k = 1..n} ( binomial(n+k,k)/(n+k)*Sum_{j = 0..k} ( binomial(j,n-k-j+1)*binomial(k,j)*(-1)^(n+k-j+1) ) ) + C(n), where C(n) is a Catalan number. - _Vladimir Kruchinin_, Nov 13 2014
Asymptotics (Klazar, 1997): a(n) ~ sqrt(5731-4635/sqrt(17)) * ((107+51*sqrt(17))/64)^n / (256 * sqrt(Pi) * n^(3/2)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Nov 14 2014

A007859.name: Number of matchings in rooted plane trees on n nodes.

A007860.name: Maximal matchings in rooted plane trees on n nodes.

A007861.name: Mahonian statistics on S_n which split (a(n)=n!.a(n-1)^n).

A007862.name: Number of triangular numbers that divide n.

A007863.name: Number of hybrid binary trees with n internal nodes.
formula: G.f.: A(x) = exp( Sum_{n>=1} [Sum_{k=0..n} C(n,k)^2*A(x)^k] * x^n/n ). - _Paul D. Hanna_, Feb 13 2011
The formal inverse of the g.f. A(x) is (sqrt(5*x^2 - 2*x + 1) - (1+x))/(2*x^2). - _Paul D. Hanna_, Aug 21 2012
The radius of convergence of g.f. A(x) is r = 0.1407810125... with A(r) = 2.1107712092... such that y=A(r) satisfies 5*y^3 - 12*y^2 + 4*y - 2 = 0. - _Paul D. Hanna_, Aug 21 2012

A007864.name: Number of matrix bundles of codimension n (Euler transform of A001156).

A007865.name: Number of sum-free subsets of {1, ..., n}.

A007866.name: Number of `homogenized' N-free graphs with n nodes.

A007867.name: Complementary pairs of `homogenized' N-free graphs with n nodes.

A007868.name: Number of inverse pairs of elements in symmetric group S_n, or pairs of total orders on n nodes (average of A000085 and A000142).

A007869.name: Number of complementary pairs of graphs on n nodes. Also number of unlabeled graphs with n nodes and an even number of edges.

A007870.name: Determinant of character table of symmetric group S_n.
formula: Product of all parts of all partitions of n.

A007871.name: Number of simple juggling patterns of n balls.

A007872.name: Sum of indices of windows of trapezoidal maps.

A007873.name: Indices of last windows of trapezoidal maps.

A007874.name: Distinct perimeter lengths of polygons with regularly spaced vertices.

A007875.name: Number of ways of writing n as p*q, with p <= q, gcd(p, q) = 1.
formula: a(n) = (1/2)*Sum_{ d divides n } abs(mu(d)) = 2^(A001221(n)-1) = A034444(n)/2, n > 1. - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Jan 25 2002
a(n) = phi(2^omega(n)) = A000010(2^A001221(n)). - _Enrique Pérez Herrero_, Apr 10 2012

Sum_{k=1..n} a(k) ~ 3*n*((log(n) + (2*gamma - 1))/ Pi^2 - 12*(Zeta'(2)/Pi^4)), where gamma is the Euler-Mascheroni constant A001620. Equivalently, Sum_{k=1..n} a(k) ~ 3*n*(log(n) + 24*log(A) - 1 - 2*log(2*Pi)) / Pi^2, where A is the Glaisher-Kinkelin constant A074962. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Jan 30 2019
a(n) = Sum_{d|n} mu(d) * A018892(n/d). - _Daniel Suteu_, Jan 08 2021

A007877.name: Period 4 zigzag sequence: repeat [0,1,2,1].
formula: Multiplicative with a(p^e) = 2 if p = 2 and e = 0; 0 if p = 2 and e > 0; 1 if p > 2. - _David W. Wilson_, Aug 01 2001
a(n) = 1 - cos(n*Pi/2); a(n) = a(n-1) - a(n-2) + a(n-3) for n>2. - Lee Reeves (leereeves(AT)fastmail.fm), May 10 2004
a(n) = 1 - T(n, 0) = 1 - A056594(n) with Chebyshev's polynomials T(n, x) of the first kind. Note that T(n, 0) = S(n, 0).
a(n) = b(n) + b(n-1), n >= 1, with b(n) := A021913(n+1) the partial sums of S(n,0) = U(n,0) = A056594(n) (Chebyshev's polynomials evaluated at x=0).
Non-reduced g.f.: x*(1+x)^2/(1-x^4). - _Jaume Oliver Lafont_, Mar 27 2009
a(n+1) = (S(n, sqrt(2))^2, n >= 0, with the Chebyshev S-polynomials A049310. See the W. Lang link under A181878. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, Dec 15 2010
a(n) = n mod 4 - 2*(((n-2 mod 4) mod 3) mod 2). - _Paolo P. Lava_, Mar 13 2011
a(n) = (n mod 4) - (n^3 mod 4) + (n^2 mod 4). - _Gary Detlefs_, Apr 17 2011]
a(n) = sqrt(n^2 mod 8). - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Jan 01 2014
a(n) = (n AND 4*k+2)-(n AND 4*k+1) + 2*floor(((n+2) mod 4)/3), for any k. - _Gary Detlefs_, Jun 08 2014

A007878.name: Number of terms in discriminant of generic polynomial of degree n.

A007879.name: Chimes made by clock striking the hour and half-hour.

A007881.name: Erroneous version of A001357 printed by mistake on back cover of Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences.

A007882.name: Number of lattice points inside circle of radius n is 4(a(n)+n)-3.

A007884.name: Chimes made by clock striking quarter-hours.

A007885.name: Numbers n such that balanced sequences exist with n distinct elements.

A007886.name: Number of cycles induced by iterating the Gray-coding of an n-bit number: a(n+1) = a(n) + ( 2^n / C_n), where C_n = least power of 2 >= n (C_n is the length of the cycle).

A007887.name: a(n) = Fibonacci(n) mod 9.
formula: Period 24 = A001175(9). Proof: F_{n+24} = F_n + 9*(5152 F_{n+1} + 3184 F_n). - Olivier Wittenberg, following a conjecture by _Ralf Stephan_, Sep 28 2004
The numbers have period 24 since F_{n+24} = F_n + 9*(5152 F_{n+1} + 3184 F_n). - Olivier Wittenberg, Sep 28 2004

A007888.name: Euler characteristic of mapping class group Gamma_n.

A007889.name: Number of intransitive (or alternating, or Stanley) trees: vertices are [0,n] and for no i<j<k are both (i,j) and (j,k) edges.
formula: E.g.f. A(x) satisfies: A(x) = exp( x*(1 + A(x))/2 ). E.g.f. A(x) equals the inverse function of 2*log(x)/(1+x). - _Paul D. Hanna_, Mar 29 2008
From _Vladeta Jovovic_ and _Paul D. Hanna_, Apr 03 2008: (Start)
Powers of e.g.f.: If A(x)^p = Sum_{n>=0} a(n,p)*x^n/n! then a(n,p) = (1/2^n)* Sum_{k=0..n} binomial(n,k)*p*(k+p)^(n-1).

Let A(x) = e.g.f. of A007889, B(x) = e.g.f. of A138860 where B(x) = exp( x*[B(x) + B(x)^2]/2 ); then B(x) = A(x*B(x)) = (1/x)*Series_Reversion(x/A(x)) and A(x) = B(x/A(x)) = x/Series_Reversion(x*B(x)). (End)
For n>0, a(n) = A088789(n+1)*2/(n+1). [_Vaclav Kotesovec_, Dec 26 2011]

A007890.name: Summarize the previous term! (in decreasing order).

A007894.name: Number of fullerenes with 2n vertices (or carbon atoms).
formula: a(n) = 809/2612138803200*sigma_9(n) + O(n^8) where sigma_9(n) is the ninth divisor power sum, cf. A013957. - _Philip Engel_, Nov 29 2017

A007895.name: Number of terms in Zeckendorf representation of n (write n as a sum of non-consecutive distinct Fibonacci numbers).

A007897.name: a(n) is multiplicative with a(2) = 1; a(4) = 2; a(2^i) = 2^(i-2)+2 if i>2; a(p^i) = 1+(p-1)*p^(i-1)/2 if prime p>2 and i>0.

A007898.name: a(n) = psi_c(n), where Product_{k>1} 1/(1-1/k^s)^A007897(k) = Sum_{k>0} psi_c(k)/k^s.

A007900.name: Coordination sequence for D_4 lattice.
formula: G.f. for coordination sequence of D_n lattice: (Sum(binomial(2*n, 2*i)*z^i, i=0..n)-2*n*z*(1+z)^(n-2))/(1-z)^n.

A007901.name: Number of minimal unavoidable n-celled pebbling configurations.
formula: G.f.: x^3*((1-3*x+x^2)*sqrt(1-4*x)-1+5*x-x^2-6*x^3)/(1-7*x+14*x^2-9*x^3) [from the Stanley reference]. - _Joerg Arndt_, Apr 20 2011

A007902.name: Number of pebbling configurations with n pebbles.

A007903.name: The number of distinct principal ideals in the semigroup of binary relations on an n-set.

A007905.name: Conflicts during insertions into exchange trees on n nodes.

A007906.name: Number of steps for aliquot sequence for n to converge to 0, or -1 if it never reaches 0.

A007907.name: Concatenation of sequence (1, 2, ..., floor((n-1)/2), floor(n/2), floor(n/2)-1, ..., 1) for n >= 1.

A007908.name: Triangle of the gods: to get a(n), concatenate the decimal numbers 1,2,3,...,n.
formula: a(n) = a(n-1)*10^floor(log_10(10*n)) + n. - _Paolo P. Lava_, Feb 01 2008
a(n) = floor(C*10^(A058183(n))) with C the Champernowne constant, 0.123456789101112131415..., A033307. - _José de Jesús Camacho Medina_, Aug 19 2015

A007909.name: Expansion of (1-x)/(1-2*x+x^2-2*x^3).
formula: a(n) = 2*a(n-1)-a(n-2)+2*a(n-3). Sequence is identical to its half second differences from the second term; a(n)+a(n+2)=2^(n+1). - _Paul Curtz_, Dec 17 2007

A007910.name: Expansion of 1/((1-2*x)*(1+x^2)).
formula: a(0) = 1, a(2n+1) = 2*a(2n) and a(2n) = 2*a(2n-1) + (-1)^n. [Corrected by _M. F. Hasler_, Feb 22 2018]
a(n) = 2a(n-1)-a(n-2)+2a(n-3). Sequence equals half its second differences with first term dropped. a(n) + a(n+2) = 2^(n+2). - _Paul Curtz_, Dec 17 2007

A007912.name: Quantum factorials: (n-1)!!-(n-2)!! (mod n).
formula: a(n) = 0 iff n is odd and not a prime congruent to 3 modulo 4. - _Charlie Neder_, Feb 24 2019

A007913.name: Squarefree part of n: a(n) is the smallest positive number m such that n/m is a square.
formula: Multiplicative with a(p^k) = p^(k mod 2). - _David W. Wilson_, Aug 01 2001
a(n) modulo 2 = A035263(n); a(A036554(n)) is even; a(A003159(n)) is odd. - _Philippe Deléham_, Mar 28 2004
Dirichlet g.f.: zeta(2s)*zeta(s-1)/zeta(2s-2). - _R. J. Mathar_, Feb 11 2011
a(n) = n/( Sum_{k=1..n} floor(k^2/n)-floor((k^2 -1)/n) )^2. - _Anthony Browne_, Jun 06 2016
a(n) = rad(n)/a(n/rad(n)), where rad = A007947. This recurrence relation together with a(1) = 1 generate the sequence. - _Velin Yanev_, Sep 19 2017
Theorems proven by Copil and Panaitopol (2007):
Sum_{k=1..n} 1/a(k) ~ c*sqrt(n) + O(log(n)), where c = zeta(3/2)/zeta(3) (A090699). (End)

A007916.name: Numbers that are not perfect powers.
formula: Gcd(exponents in prime factorization of a(n)) = 1, cf. A124010. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Apr 13 2012
a(n) ~ n. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Jul 01 2013

A007917.name: Version 1 of the "previous prime" function: largest prime <= n.
formula: For n >= 2, a(A000203(n)) = A070801(n). - _Antti Karttunen_, Nov 07 2017

A007918.name: Least prime >= n (version 1 of the "next prime" function).

A007919.name: Smallest k such that k*n is a double factorial.

A007920.name: Smallest number k such that n + k is prime.

A007921.name: Numbers that are not the difference of two primes.

A007922.name: Smallest k such that k!! is a multiple of n.

A007923.name: Lengths increase by 1, digits cycle through positive digits.
formula: a(n) = (10^9+1) a(n-9) - 10^9 a(n-18), n>=18. - corrected by _Michael Somos_, Sep 28 2002

A007924.name: The number n written using the greedy algorithm in the base where the values of the places are 1 and primes.
formula: a(n) is the binary representation of b(n) = 2^pi(n) + b(n-p(pi(n))) for n > 0 and a(0) = b(0)= 0, where pi(k) = number of primes <= k (A000720) and p(k) = k-th prime (A008578). - _Frank Ellermann_, Dec 18 2001

A007925.name: a(n) = n^(n+1) - (n+1)^n.
formula: Asymptotic expression for a(n) is a(n) ~ n^n * (n - e). - Ahmed Fares (ahmedfares(AT)my-deja.com), Apr 19 2001

A007926.name: Some permutation of digits is a factorial number.

A007927.name: Some nontrivial permutation of digits is a factorial number.

A007928.name: Numbers containing an even digit.
formula: a(n) ~ n. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Sep 07 2012

A007929.name: Odd numbers containing an even digit.

A007930.name: Some nontrivial permutation of digits gives an even number.
formula: a(n) ~ n. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Sep 19 2012

A007931.name: Numbers that contain only 1's and 2's. Nonempty binary strings of length n in lexicographic order.
formula: To get a(n), write n+1 in base 2, remove initial 1, add 1 to all remaining digits: e.g., eleven (11) in base 2 is 1011; remove initial 1 and add 1 to remaining digits: a(10)=122. - _Clark Kimberling_, Mar 11 2003

Conversely, given a(n), to get n: subtract 1 from all digits, prefix with an initial 1, convert this binary number to base 10, subtract 1. E.g., a(6)=22 -> 11 -> 111 -> 7 -> 6. - _N. J. A. Sloane_, Jul 09 2012
The formulas are designed to calculate base-10 numbers only using the digits 1 and 2.
a(n) = Sum_{j=0..m-1} (1 + b(j) mod 2)*10^j, where m = floor(log_2(n+1)), b(j) = floor((n+1-2^m)/(2^j)).
a(n) <= (10^log_2(n+1)-1)/9, equality holds for n=2^k-1, k>0.
lim inf a(n)/10^log_2(n) = 1/45, for n --> infinity.
lim sup a(n)/10^log_2(n) = 1/9, for n --> infinity.

A007932.name: Numbers that contain only 1's, 2's and 3's.
formula: The formulas are designed to calculate base-10 numbers only using the digits 1, 2, 3.
a(n) <= (10^log_3(2*n+1)-1)/9, equality holds for n=(3^k-1)/2, k>0.
lim inf a(n)/10^log_3(2*n) = 1/30, for n --> infinity.
lim sup a(n)/10^log_3(2*n) = 1/9, for n --> infinity.

A007933.name: Some permutation of digits is a prime.

A007934.name: Some nontrivial permutation of digits is a prime.

A007935.name: Composite numbers such that some permutation of digits is a prime.

A007936.name: Some permutation of digits is a square.

A007937.name: Nonsquares such that some permutation of digits is a square.

A007938.name: Some nontrivial permutation of digits is a square.

A007939.name: Some permutation of digits is a cube.

A007940.name: Noncubes such that some permutation of digits is a cube.

A007941.name: Some nontrivial permutation of digits is a cube.

A007942.name: Decimal concatenation of sequence (n, n-1, ..., 2, 1, 2, ..., n-1, n).
formula: a(n+1) = n*10^(floor(1+log_10(a(n))) + floor(1+log_10(n))) + a(n)*10^floor(1+log_10(n))+n, with a(1)=1. - _Paolo P. Lava_, Jun 04 2008

A007944.name: Largest even number a(n) such that 6,8,...,a(n) are sums of 2 of first n odd primes.
formula: a(n) << n log n. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Sep 19 2012
More specifically, a(n) <= 2*prime(n+1). On the Goldbach conjecture a(n) >= prime(n+1) + 3. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Dec 09 2014

A007946.name: a(n) = 6*(2*n+1)! / ((n!)^2*(n+3)).
formula: a(n) = C(2n+2, n) + C(2n+3, n). - _Emeric Deutsch_, May 16 2003

Representation as the n-th moment of a signed function: w(x) = sqrt(x/(4-x))*(x^2-2*x-2)/Pi on the segment x=(0,4). In Maple notation: a(n) = int(x^n*w(x), x=0..4). For x->0, w(x)->0, and for x->4, w(x)->infinity.
a(x) ~ exp(x*log(4)-(log(Pi)+cos(2*Pi*x)*(log(x) + 1/(4*x)))/2 + log((12*x+6)/ (3+x))). For example, this formula gives a(100) = 0.10602088... *10^61.

A007947.name: Largest squarefree number dividing n: the squarefree kernel of n, rad(n), radical of n.
formula: If n = Product_j (p_j^k_j) where p_j are distinct primes, then a(n) = Product_j (p_j).
Dirichlet g.f.: zeta(s)*Product_{primes p} (1+p^(1-s)-p^(-s)). - _R. J. Mathar_, Jan 21 2012
a(n) = Sum_{d|n} phi(d) * mu(d)^2. - _Enrique Pérez Herrero_, Apr 23 2012
a(n) = Product_{d|n} d^(moebius(n/d)) (see Billal link). - _Michel Marcus_, Jan 06 2015
a(n) = n/( Sum_{k=1..n} (floor(k^n/n)-floor((k^n - 1)/n)) ) = e^(Sum_{k=2..n} (floor(n/k) - floor((n-1)/k))*A010051(k)*M(k)) where M(n) is the Mangoldt function. - _Anthony Browne_, Jun 17 2016
G.f.: Sum_{k>=1} phi(k)*mu(k)^2*x^k/(1 - x^k). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Apr 11 2017
Dirichlet g.f.: zeta(s-1) * zeta(s) * Product_{primes p} (1 + p^(1-2*s) - p^(2-2*s) - p^(-s)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Dec 18 2019
Sum_{k=1..n} a(k) ~ c * n^2, where c = A065463/2. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Jun 24 2020

A007948.name: Largest cubefree number dividing n.
formula: Multiplicative with a(p^e) = p^(min(e, 2)). - _David W. Wilson_, Aug 01 2001
a(n) = A071773(n)*A007947(n). - observed by _Velin Yanev_, Aug 20 2017, confirmed by _Antti Karttunen_, Nov 28 2017

A007949.name: Greatest k such that 3^k divides n. Or, 3-adic valuation of n.
formula: a(n) = 0 if n != 0 (mod 3), otherwise a(n) = 1 + a(n/3). - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Aug 12 2001, edited by _M. F. Hasler_, Aug 11 2015
Fixed point of the morphism: 0 -> 001; 1 -> 002; 2 -> 003; 3 -> 004; 4 -> 005; etc.; starting from a(1) = 0. - _Philippe Deléham_, Mar 29 2004
Totally additive with a(p) = 1 if p = 3, 0 otherwise.

v_{m}(n) = Sum_{r>=1} (r/m^(r+1)) Sum_{j=1..m-1} Sum_{k=0..m^(r+1)-1} exp((2*k*Pi*i*(n+(m-j)*m^r)) / m^(r+1)). This formula is for the general case; for this specific one, set m=3. - _A. Neves_, Oct 04 2010
a(3n) = a(n) + 1, a(pn) = a(n) for any other prime p != 3. - _M. F. Hasler_, Aug 11 2015
Asymptotic mean: lim_{m->oo} (1/m) * Sum_{k=1..m} a(k) = 1/2. - _Amiram Eldar_, Jul 11 2020
a(n) = tau(n)/(tau(3*n) - tau(n)) - 1, where tau(n) = A000005(n). - _Peter Bala_, Jan 06 2021

A007950.name: Binary sieve: delete every 2nd number, then every 4th, 8th, etc.

A007951.name: Ternary sieve: delete every 3rd number, then every 9th, 27th, etc.

A007952.name: Generated by a sieve: keep first number, drop every 2nd, keep first, drop every 3rd, keep first, drop every 4th, etc.

A007953.name: Digital sum (i.e., sum of digits) of n; also called digsum(n).
formula: a(n) = n - 9*Sum_{10 <= k <= n} Sum_{j|k, j >= 10} floor(log_10(j)) - floor(log_10(j-1)). (End)

The g.f. can be expressed in terms of a Lambert series, in that g(x) = (x/(1-x) - 9*L[b(k)](x))/(1-x) where L[b(k)](x) = sum{k >= 0, b(k)*x^k/(1-x^k)} is a Lambert series with b(k) = 1, if k > 1 is a power of 10, else b(k) = 0.
G.f.: g(x) = (Sum_{k > 0} (1 - 9*c(k))*x^k)/(1-x), where c(k) = Sum_{j > 1, j|k} floor(log_10(j)) - floor(log_10(j-1)).
a(n) <= 9*(1 + floor(log_10(n)), equality holds for n = 10^m - 1, m > 0.
lim inf (a(n+1) - a(n) + 9*log_10(n)) = 1 for n --> infinity. (End)
a(n) = A138530(n, 10) for n > 9. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Mar 26 2008
a(n) = a(n-1) + a(n-10) - a(n-11), for n < 100. - _Alexander R. Povolotsky_, Oct 09 2011
a(n) = Sum_{k >= 0} A031298(n, k). - _Philippe Deléham_, Oct 21 2011
a(n) = a(n mod b^k) + a(floor(n/b^k)), for all k >= 0. - _Hieronymus Fischer_, Mar 24 2014

A007954.name: Product of decimal digits of n.
formula: a(n) > 0 if and only if A054054(n) > 0. a(n) = d in {1, ..., 9} if n = (10^k - 1)/9 + (d - 1)*10^m = A002275(k) + (d - 1)*A011557(m) for some k > m >= 0. The statement holds with "if and only if" for d in {1, 2, 3, 5, 7}. For d = 4, 6, 8 or 9, one has a(n) = d if n = (10^k - 1)/9 + (a - 1)*10^m + (b - 1)*10^p with integers k > m > p >= 0 and a, b > 0 such that d = a*b. - _M. F. Hasler_, Oct 11 2015

A007955.name: Product of divisors of n.
formula: a(n) = n^(d(n)/2) = n^(A000005(n)/2). Since a(n) = Product_(d|n) d = Product_(d|n) n/d, we have a(n)*a(n) = Product_(d|n) d*(n/d) = Product_(d|n) n = n^(tau(n)), whence a(n) = n^(tau(n)/2).
A001222(a(n)) = A069264(n). [See _Geoffrey Critzer_'s Feb 03 2015 comment in the latter sequence.]

A007956.name: Product of proper divisors of n.
formula: a(n) = A007955(n)/n = n^(A000005(n)/2-1) = sqrt(n^(number of factors of n other than 1 and n)).
a(n) = A240694(n, A000005(n)-1) for n > 1. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Apr 10 2014

A007957.name: Numbers that contain an odd digit.
formula: a(n) = n + O(n^0.69897...) where the constant is A153268. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Jul 25 2012

A007958.name: Even numbers with at least one odd digit.

A007959.name: Some nontrivial permutation of digits is an odd number.

A007967.name: Second factor in happy factorization of n.

A007968.name: Type of happy factorization of n.

A007969.name: Rectangular numbers.
formula: a(n) is in the sequence if a(n) = C*B with integers B >= 1 and C >= 2, such that C*S^2 - B*R^2 = 1 has an integer solution (without loss of generality one may take S and R positive). See the Conway link. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, Sep 18 2015

A007970.name: Rhombic numbers.
formula: a(n) is in the sequence if a(n) = D*E with positive integers D and E, such that E*U^2 - D*T^2 = 2 has an integer solution with U*T odd (without loss of generality one may take U and T positive). See the Conway link. D and E are given in A191856 and A191857, respectively. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, Oct 05 2015

A007971.name: INVERTi transform of central trinomial coefficients (A002426).
formula: A002426(n) = Sum_{i=1..n} a(i)*A002426(n-i), n>0. - _Michael Somos_, Jun 14 2000
G.f.: 1-sqrt(1-2*x-3*(x^2)) =  x/G(0) ; G(k) = 1-2*x/(1+x/(1+x/(1-2*x/(1-x/(2-x/G(k+1)))))) ; (continued fraction). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Dec 11 2011

A007972.name: Number of permutations that are 2 "block reversals" away from 12...n.
formula: Conjectured g.f.: (-2-5x+3x^2+x^3-x^4)/(-1+x)^5. - _Benedict W. J. Irwin_, Feb 20 2016

A007973.name: Number of permutations that are n-2 "block reversals" away from 12...n.

A007978.name: Least non-divisor of n.
formula: a(n!) = prime(pi(n) + 1) for n >= 0, except for a(3!) = 4. (End)

A007980.name: Expansion of (1+x^2)/((1-x)^2*(1-x^3)).
formula: a(n) = a(n-1) + a(n-3) -a(n-4) + 2 = a(-3-n) for all n in Z. - _Michael Somos_, Jun 07 2003

formula: a(n) = A136184(n) - floor(n/2) - 1. - _Eric M. Schmidt_, Jan 08 2015

A007983.name: Number of non-Abelian metacyclic groups of order p^n (p odd).
formula: a(n) = A136185(n) - floor(n/2) - 1. - _Eric M. Schmidt_, Jan 08 2015

formula: G.f. (x+1) * sqrt(1-x) / sqrt((1-3*x) * (3*x^2+1)) [from Humphries]. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Feb 26 2018

formula: a(n+5) = Sum_{k=0..floor(n/2)} C(n-k,L(k/3)), where L(j/p) is the Legendre symbol of j and p. - _Paul Barry_, Mar 16 2006

formula: G.f.: Sum_{k>=0} E_{2k+1}^2 u^(2k+1)/(2k+1)! + (1-x^2)^(-1/2) Sum_{k>=0} E_{2k}^2 u^(2k)/(2k)!, where E_j is an Euler number (A000111) and u = (1/2)*log((1+x)/(1-x)). - _Richard Stanley_, Jan 21 2006
